		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Video: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ar9WRwCiSr0">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ar9WRwCiSr0</a><!-- m --><br />Making of: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hTlNVUmBA28">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hTlNVUmBA28</a><!-- m --><br /><br />The idea of putting a more powerful processor into a NES cartridge and expanding the abilities of the NES have been talked about and demonstrated here on nesdev before, so I guess this is not really anything new, but as a &quot;layman&quot; who follows this community with casual interest, it doesn't make this video and demonstration any less satisfying to watch.

		

