	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Only in the sense that they're both providing a stream of raw bytes to the PPU. The implementation of the two is entirely different; tom7's is a well-deserved hack through-and-through, whereas rasteri's use of an actual digital FIFO IC means he just has to generate bytes fast enough, not figure out the exact timing.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


